# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Install Rust: curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
# Extra cargo subcommands used below (install via cargo):
#   cargo-watch:   cargo install cargo-watch
#   cargo-expand:  cargo install cargo-expand
#   cargo-bloat:   cargo install cargo-bloat
#   cross:         cargo install cross   (cross-compilation, needs Docker)

# ── Build / Run ────────────────────────────────────────
alias cb='cargo build'              # debug build (fast, unoptimised, includes debug info)
alias cbr='cargo build --release'   # release build (optimised, slower to build)
alias cr='cargo run'                # build + run debug binary
alias crr='cargo run --release'     # build + run release binary

# ── Test ──────────────────────────────────────────────
alias ct='cargo test'               # run all tests
alias ctest1='cargo test -- --test-threads=1'  # single-threaded — prevents parallelism issues
                                               # when tests share global state or file handles

# ctf — run tests matching a specific name (substring match).
# cargo test filters by substring, not regex — "foo" matches test_foo and foo_bar.
# Usage: ctf my_function_name
ctf() { cargo test "$1"; }

# ── Quality / Lint ────────────────────────────────────
alias ccheck='cargo check'          # type-check without producing a binary — fastest feedback loop
alias cclippy='cargo clippy'        # Clippy linter — catches common mistakes and style issues
alias cautoclippy='cargo clippy --fix --allow-dirty'  # auto-fix Clippy warnings in dirty working tree
alias cfmt='cargo fmt'              # format all source files with rustfmt
alias cfix='cargo fix'              # auto-apply compiler-suggested fixes

# ── Docs / Analysis ───────────────────────────────────
alias cdoc='cargo doc --open'       # build and open crate docs in browser
alias cbench='cargo bench'          # run benchmarks (requires criterion or built-in bench)
alias cexpand='cargo expand'        # expand macros to plain Rust — needs cargo-expand
alias csize='cargo bloat --release' # show which functions contribute most to binary size — needs cargo-bloat

# ── Dependency management ─────────────────────────────
alias cadd='cargo add'              # add dependency to Cargo.toml: cadd serde --features derive
alias crm='cargo remove'            # remove dependency from Cargo.toml
alias cup='cargo update'            # update Cargo.lock to latest compatible versions

# ── Hot-reload ────────────────────────────────────────
alias cwatch='cargo watch -x run'   # rebuild + rerun on any file change — needs cargo-watch
                                    # Usage: cwatch          (watch src/)
                                    #        cwatch -x test  (watch + retest)

# ── Cross-compilation ─────────────────────────────────
# cross uses Docker to provide the correct linker + sysroot for the target.
# Usage: cross-build aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu
#        cross-build thumbv7em-none-eabihf   (embedded ARM Cortex-M4)
cross-build() { cross build --target "$1" --release; }


# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# FZF
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# fzf is the fuzzy-finder engine used by many functions below.
# Shell keybindings (sourced from fzf's own shell integration):
#   Ctrl+T — fuzzy-insert a file path at the current cursor position
#   Ctrl+R — fuzzy-search shell history (overridden by atuin when installed)
#   Alt+C  — fuzzy-cd into a subdirectory
[[ -f ~/.fzf.zsh ]] && source ~/.fzf.zsh
[[ -f /opt/homebrew/opt/fzf/shell/key-bindings.zsh ]] && \
  source /opt/homebrew/opt/fzf/shell/key-bindings.zsh

# Catppuccin Mocha colour theme — matches the Neovim / tmux colour scheme.
# --border rounded  — use rounded box-drawing characters for the frame
# --prompt / --pointer / --marker — Unicode glyphs for UI chrome
# --height 50%      — occupy half the terminal height (not full-screen)
# --layout reverse  — show results from top-to-bottom (most relevant at top)
export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS="
  --color=bg+:#313244,bg:#1e1e2e,spinner:#f5e0dc,hl:#f38ba8
  --color=fg:#cdd6f4,header:#f38ba8,info:#cba6f7,pointer:#f5e0dc
  --color=marker:#b4befe,fg+:#cdd6f4,prompt:#cba6f7,hl+:#f38ba8
  --border rounded --prompt '❯ ' --pointer '▶' --marker '✔'
  --height 50% --layout reverse
"

# fd is used as the file finder backend for fzf:
# --hidden        — include dotfiles
# --follow        — follow symlinks
# --exclude .git  — skip .git directories
export FZF_DEFAULT_COMMAND='fd --type f --hidden --follow --exclude .git'
export FZF_CTRL_T_COMMAND="$FZF_DEFAULT_COMMAND"
export FZF_ALT_C_COMMAND='fd --type d --hidden --follow --exclude .git'

# fglog — fuzzy git log browser.
# Shows one-line commit log in fzf; the right pane shows the full diff
# for the highlighted commit. Press Enter to print the SHA (useful for
# piping into git show, git cherry-pick, etc.).
# Usage: fglog
#        git cherry-pick $(fglog)
fglog() {
  git log --oneline --color=always | \
    fzf --ansi --preview 'git show --color=always {1}' \
        --preview-window=right:60% | \
    awk '{print $1}'
}

# fcd — fuzzy cd into any subdirectory of the current location.
# Preview pane shows the first level of the selected directory.
# Usage: fcd
fcd() {
  local dir
  dir=$(fd --type d --hidden --exclude .git | \
    fzf --preview 'eza --tree --level=1 --icons {}') && cd "$dir"
}

# fkill — fuzzy process killer.
# Lists all processes in fzf; selecting one sends SIGKILL.
# Usage: fkill   (select process, press Enter)
fkill() {
  local pid
  pid=$(ps aux | fzf --header='Select process to kill' | awk '{print $2}')
  [[ -n "$pid" ]] && kill -9 "$pid" && echo "Killed $pid"
}

# fenv — fuzzy env var picker. Copies the VALUE of the selected
# variable to the macOS clipboard.
# Usage: fenv   (pick a var, its value is in clipboard)
fenv() {
  local val
  val=$(env | sort | fzf --prompt='env> ' | cut -d= -f2-)
  [[ -n "$val" ]] && echo "$val" | pbcopy && echo "Copied: $val"
}

# falias — fuzzy alias browser.
# Lists all defined aliases; selecting one prints its expansion.
# Useful for discovering aliases you defined but forgot.
# Usage: falias
falias() {
  alias | fzf --prompt='alias> ' | sed 's/=/: /'
}

# fman — fuzzy man page picker.
# Searches all installed man page topics; preview pane shows the first
# 40 lines of the page. Press Enter to open in the full man pager.
# Usage: fman
fman() {
  local page
  page=$(man -k . 2>/dev/null | fzf --prompt='man> ' \
    --preview 'echo {} | awk "{print \$1}" | xargs man 2>/dev/null | head -40' | \
    awk '{print $1}')
  [[ -n "$page" ]] && man "$page"
}

# fssh — fuzzy SSH host picker.
# Reads Host entries from ~/.ssh/config (excluding wildcards) and opens
# an SSH connection to the selected host.
# Usage: fssh
fssh() {
  local host
  host=$(grep -E "^Host " ~/.ssh/config 2>/dev/null | awk '{print $2}' | \
    grep -v '\*' | fzf --prompt='ssh> ')
  [[ -n "$host" ]] && ssh "$host"
}

# fbr — fuzzy branch checkout.
# Lists all local and remote branches; preview pane shows the last few
# commits on that branch. Press Enter to check it out.
# Usage: fbr
fbr() {
  local branch
  branch=$(git branch -a --color=always | grep -v '/HEAD\s' | \
    fzf --ansi --preview 'git log --oneline --color=always $(echo {} | sed "s/.* //")' \
        --preview-window=right:50% | \
    sed 's/.* //' | sed 's|remotes/[^/]*/||')
  [[ -n "$branch" ]] && git checkout "$branch"
}

# fstash — fuzzy stash picker.
# Lists all stash entries; preview pane shows the stash diff.
# Press Enter to apply the selected stash (non-destructive: stash stays).
# Usage: fstash
fstash() {
  local stash
  stash=$(git stash list | fzf --prompt='stash> ' \
    --preview 'git stash show -p $(echo {} | cut -d: -f1)' \
    --preview-window=right:60% | cut -d: -f1)
  [[ -n "$stash" ]] && git stash apply "$stash"
}


